## Common commands

```bash
flutter pub get
dart run build_runner build
flutter gen-l10n
dart format .
flutter analyze
flutter test
# Emulator Suite — health-check the hub; start it if down (seeds round-trip):
curl -s http://localhost:4441
firebase emulators:start --project demo-<app> --import .firebase/seed --export-on-exit .firebase/seed
# Stop the suite (frees the ports; --export-on-exit writes the seed on the way out):
lsof -ti :4441 | xargs kill
# Headless test runs (emulators start + clean up automatically):
firebase emulators:exec --project demo-<app> --import .firebase/seed \
  "flutter test integration_test/ --dart-define=APP_ENV=dev -d <ios-sim>"
# Run / test the dev flavor (emulators) on a simulator:
flutter run --dart-define=APP_ENV=dev -d <device>
flutter test integration_test/ --dart-define=APP_ENV=dev -d <ios-sim>
flutter test integration_test/ --dart-define=APP_ENV=dev -d <android-emu>  # (Android — on explicit request)
xcrun simctl io "iPhone 16 Pro" screenshot /tmp/screenshot.png
adb exec-out screencap -p > docs/screenshots/<name>.png  # (Android — on explicit request)
```

## Codegen workflow

Generated files are committed. Workflow:

1. Edit `*.dart` annotated with `@freezed`, `@JsonSerializable`, etc.
2. Run `dart run build_runner build`.
3. Commit the generated files.

## Verification

After implementing a feature, `/step` (via the `flutter-qa` agent) gates on:
1. `flutter analyze` — clean.
2. `flutter test` — all unit/bloc/widget tests pass.
3. Dev flavor runs on the **iOS simulator** against the running **Firebase
   Emulator Suite** — so the prod repository impls and security rules are
   exercised continuously; the new flow's happy + error/edge paths and **every
   dependent flow** are exercised via `integration_test`.
   For steps touching `android/` or Android-specific behavior, add a one-line
   non-blocking note: recommend an explicit Android `/qa` sweep.
4. **Zero runtime errors/exceptions** in the Dart MCP error log during the runs.
5. **Zero render (overflow) errors** across the responsive size matrix (see
   `PRODUCT_SPEC.md` → Non-functional) at textScale 1.0 and 2.0.
6. Successful flows captured as permanent integration tests; screenshots only as
   FAIL evidence (the multi-size visual sweep runs in `/qa` and pre-`/ship`).

The **Backend integration pass** plan step (immediately before release prep) is
the final real-backend checkpoint: prod flavor on the iOS simulator against the
real **STAGING** Firebase project, rules + indexes deployed first, core flows
driven, zero unhandled exceptions to pass.

